49
00:03:35,920 --> 00:03:37,820
What's the problem, Dennis?

50
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:40,700
Veronica, where exactly was
this tumor supposed to be?

51
00:03:40,720 --> 00:03:41,870
On the right kidney.

52
00:03:41,880 --> 00:03:43,810
It's on the MRI scan and the ultrasound.

53
00:03:43,820 --> 00:03:44,720
Taken when?

54
00:03:44,740 --> 00:03:46,020
Three weeks ago.

55
00:03:46,050 --> 00:03:47,840
Well, look at the ultrasound now.

56
00:03:47,870 --> 00:03:50,210
I checked the other one,
too, just to be safe.

57
00:03:50,220 --> 00:03:52,580
This boy's kidneys are
immaculate. Perfectly normal.

58
00:03:52,590 --> 00:03:55,230
That's not possible. I
performed the exam myself.

59
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,300
The tumor was right there.

60
00:03:57,320 --> 00:03:59,860
Well, it's not there now.

61
00:04:05,390 --> 00:04:09,200
People are flocking to what is
being called a miracle spring,

62
00:04:09,230 --> 00:04:15,570
which suddenly appeared during the heavy storms that
hit Lewiston, Montana a little over three weeks ago.

63
00:04:15,580 --> 00:04:17,560
Now, this is eight-year-old
Nicholas Harris,

64
00:04:17,570 --> 00:04:20,880
who was diagnosed with a
cancerous tumor on his kidney,

65
00:04:20,910 --> 00:04:26,550
