mysterious spring, the tumor just disappeared.

66
00:04:26,570 --> 00:04:29,740
The boy's father
believes it was a miracle.

67
00:04:31,910 --> 00:04:34,640
<i></i>

68
00:04:38,090 --> 00:04:40,160
What the...

69
00:04:44,320 --> 00:04:47,100
- Hood?
- Hey, Rachel, you seen this?

70
00:04:52,500 --> 00:04:54,530
Hood, what are you doing here?

71
00:04:54,550 --> 00:04:56,640
- Nice place.
- Hood, it's Sunday.

72
00:04:56,650 --> 00:04:59,310
Rachel, you have to see this.

73
00:04:59,320 --> 00:05:01,930
I have to see this?

74
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:06,380
Miracle boy.

75
00:05:06,390 --> 00:05:09,190
Miracle cure for cancer found.

76
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:11,050
Miracle spring.

77
00:05:11,060 --> 00:05:13,900
Okay, I saw them. Are you happy?

78
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:16,550
Hood, it's Sunday and it's 6:00 A.M.

79
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:21,130
Rachel... we have to
go to Montana right now.

80
00:05:21,140 --> 00:05:24,190
No. No, no, no, no. Please,
please don't. I'm begging you.

81
00:05:24,200 --> 00:05:28,720
If this is my weekend free of all
things "Hood," unless this is a dream.

82
00:05:28,730 --> 00:05:30,890
Is this a dream?

83
00:05:37,990 --> 00:05:42,900
Actually, you know what,
uh, I just realized...

84
00:05:42,910 --> 00:05:46,190
I think I could be able
to do this on my own, huh?

85
00:05:47,150 --> 00:05:49,620
Wait.

86
00:05:50,120 --> 00:05:56,080
I need an airtight, seamless, indestructible reason
to leave my apartment before 7:00 A.M.Monday morning.

87
00:05:56,110 --> 00:05:58,150
Let's hear it.

88
00:05:59,120 --> 00:06:01,410
Okay.

89
00:06:03,660 --> 00:06:09,920
If this causes very sick people to walk away from
their medical treatment to drink from this spring,

90
00:06:10,410 --> 00:06:12,550
they're going to die.

91
00:06:12,560 --> 00:06:15,450
That'll do. Turn around.

92
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:18,800
Turn around.

93
00:06:22,140 --> 00:06:24,710
How'd you find my place, anyway?

94
00:06:24,720 --> 00:06:27,990
Oh, the FBI has its resources, Rachel.

95
00:06:29,130 --> 00:06:32,120
Anyway, what about Mr. Shoes?

96
00:06:33,790 --> 00:06:35,790
Don't worry.

97
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:38,470
He'll wait.

98
00:06:38,490 --> 00:06:40,600
So, Hood,

99
00:06:43,200 --> 00:06:46,810
what if we get to Montana and
realize it really is a miracle?

100
00:06:47,660 --> 00:06:49,950
Oh, take it from me, Rachel.

101
00:06:51,340 --> 00:06:55,700
There's no... such... thing.

